Merchant Admin API Contracts (React SPA ↔ Java) – Locked Specification

Scope

This document locks the authenticated API contracts used by the Merchant Admin (React SPA) for:
	•	Authentication & tenant selection
	•	Staff management (invite/reset)
	•	Site editing (Java → Payload gateway)
	•	Store management (products, categories, images, linked products)
	•	Order operations (confirm, fulfill, mark paid, refund)

This spec follows the locked API Design Conventions:
	•	Base: /api/v1/...
	•	Tenant scoping: /api/v1/tenants/{tenantId}/... and must match token tenantId
	•	Offset pagination with { data, page, pageSize, total }
	•	Filtering via query params, search q, sorting sort=field:dir
	•	RFC7807-like errors with traceId

⸻

1) Authentication & Session APIs

1.1 Login

POST /api/v1/auth/login

Request:

{ "email": "user@x.com", "password": "..." }

Response (one membership):

{
  "mode": "SIGNED_IN",
  "tenant": { "tenantId": "uuid", "name": "Coco Cosmetics" },
  "accessToken": "jwt",
  "accessTokenExpiresInSeconds": 900
}

Response (multiple memberships):

{
  "mode": "TENANT_SELECTION_REQUIRED",
  "preAuthToken": "jwt-preauth",
  "tenants": [ { "tenantId": "uuid", "name": "Coco Cosmetics" } ]
}

Notes:
	•	Refresh token is set as httpOnly cookie only after tenant selection (or single membership).

⸻

1.2 Select tenant

POST /api/v1/auth/select-tenant

Headers:
