8) Error Handling (Locked)
	•	All errors follow RFC7807-like structure with traceId.
	•	401 for unauthenticated
	•	403 for unauthorized
	•	404 for not found within tenant scope
	•	409 for conflicts (slug/sku uniqueness)
	•	422 optional for validation; 400 acceptable for MVP

⸻

9) Final Locked Summary

Merchant Admin uses /api/v1/... with tenant scoping in path and token.

Locked endpoint areas:
	•	Auth/session: login, select-tenant, refresh, logout, switch-tenant
	•	Session context: /me
	•	Staff management: list/invite/change role/disable
	•	Site edit (Payload gateway): settings + pages
	•	Store management: categories, products, images, linked products
	•	Orders operations: list/detail/confirm/status changes/mark paid/refund
	•	Payment settings (admin-only): Wompi config

All endpoints align with:
	•	centralized policy actions
	•	capability gating (CAP_STORE)
	•	audit event requirements
	•	API conventions (pagination/filter/sort/errors)

This specification is locked and implementation-ready.